    "number": 11698,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[Kernel][Triton][AMD] Use block size heuristic for avg 2.8x speedup for int8 models",
    "user": {
      "login": "rasmith",
      "id": 98028,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk4MDI4",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98028?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/rasmith",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rasmith/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Use the heuristic from scaled_mm_c3x_sm90_int8_dispatch.cuh:116 to choose block-size for triton_scaled_mm instead of always using 32x32x32 for better performance.  This results in average 2.8x speedup.\n\nI ran: \npython benchmarks/benchmark_latency.py --dtype bfloat16 --enable-chunked-prefill False --load-format dummy --batch-size BS --num-iters-warmup 2 --num-iters 5 --input-len INPUT_LEN --output-len OUTPUT_LEN --model MODEL\n\nwhere\n```python\nBS in [1, 16, 64]\nINPUT_LEN in [128, 1024, 2048]\nOUTPUT_LEN in [1, 128, 1024]\nMODEL in [\"Qwen2-7B-Instruct-quantized.w8a8\", \"Phi-3-medium-128k-instruct-quantized.w8a8\", \n                  \"Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct-quantized.w8a8\", \"Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3-quantized.w8a8\"]\n```\nto get this number.\n\nHere are a few samples for Qwen2-7B-Instruct-quantized.w8a8 with dtype = bfloat16\n\n| batch_size | input_len | output_len | avg_latency_old | avg_latency_new | speedup |\n|------------|-----------|------------|-----------------|-----------------|---------|\n| 1          | 128       | 128        | 1.4206          | 0.9828          | 1.4453  |\n| 1          | 1024      | 1024       | 11.4586         | 7.8414          | 1.4612  |\n| 64         | 2048      | 128        | 14.2707         | 4.7842          | 2.9828  |\n\nI uploaded the full CSV file for all of the models and configs.\n\n[heuristic_speedups.csv](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/18339277/heuristic_speedups.csv)\n",
    "created_at": "2025-01-03T00:31:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-01-08T20:23:16Z",
